GHOST OF KHOZAN was reluctant to load, broke well and vied inside, could not kick on from upper stretch, was forced in a bit in mid-stretch at the gap, faded. FACTUM LOVE STYLE angled in and was unhurried at the rear early, came out for the stretch run and passed foes. THE FIRE WITHIN raced toward the rear two to three wide, needed more. MINTENON was forwardly-positioned between runners, forced the pace up the backstretch, retreated. EMOTIONAL RESCUE bumped the outer foe and steadied at the start, was forwardly-positioned stalking just off the leading trio two to three wide, dropped back and tired. MR. COWBOY BRADLEY was lightly brushed at the start, gained forward position in pursuit of the leaders tucking in two to three wide into the first turn, dropped back from the three-eighths and faded.
